# Add 3D Shaders to Originals

This plan outlines the steps to add powerful new 3D shaders to the "aSS Originals (2024)" screensaver mix, while ensuring we do not touch or ruin the classic effects used in other categories.

## Proposed Changes

### src/js/effects.js
#### [MODIFY] effects.js
- Add `matrix3d`: A high-fidelity 3D Digital Rain shader, giving it perspective, glowing characters, and a much more powerful visual aesthetic. The classic `matrix` effect will be untouched.
- Add `cyberpipes`: A neon/cyberpunk raymarched variant of 3D pipes with glowing emissions. The classic `pipes` effect will be untouched.
- Add `voxelcity`: A 3D raymarched flight through an endless neon schematic city.

- Modify `pipes_ag` to include a structured `settings` panel allowing the user to tweak its parameters (like color speed, pipe thickness, etc.) to match the customizability of the classic `pipes`.
- Add `warp_ag`: High-speed raymarched star warp.
- Add `rain_ag`: Cinematic 3D rain simulation.
- Add `aurora_ag`: Volumetric Northern Lights shader.
- Add `neongrid_ag`: 80s synthwave retrowave landscape.
- Add `glplanet_ag`: High-detail 3D Earth planet with atmosphere.
- Add `hyperspace_ag`: Multi-dimensional tunnel.
- Add `timetunnel_ag`: Clock/time themed dimensional rift.
- Add `helios_ag`: Volumetric sun/plasma sphere.
- Add `fireflies_ag`: Interactive glowing boids.
- Add `electropaint_ag`: Fluid simulation paint trails.
Note: All new shaders will have ` -Antigravity` in their descriptions and will not replace the classic implementations in other categories.

